David see here: http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/microsoft.sqlserver.management.common.aspx&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The Microsoft.SqlServer.Management.Common namespace resides in the Microsoft.SqlServer.ConnectionInfo.dll assembly file.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
By using the Microsoft.SqlServer.Management.Common namespace, you can do the following:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Connect to an instance of SQL Server.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Control the connection settings.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Run Transact-SQL statements directly.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Capture the Transact-SQL statements that are generated by the SMO program.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Manage transactions.

Sql Server 2008&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Visual Studio 2008&lt;br /&gt;
